text: Annika Beck and Laura Siegemund were the defending champions, but chose not to participate this year. Lyudmyla and Nadiia Kichenok won the title, defeating Tímea Babos and Réka Luca Jani in the final, 6–3, 6–1. ==Seeds== The top two seeds received a bye into the quarterfinals. ==Draw== ===Bracket=== == References == * Main Draw Brasil Tennis Cup - Doubles 2016 Doubles
